  <h1 id="title">Lion King</h1>
  <p>The king of the jungle</p>
  <figure id="img-div">
    <img id="image" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Lion in the jungle">
    <figcaption id="img-caption">
        In the heart of the jungle, the majestic lion prowls with regal authority, its golden mane a symbol of strength and dominance. As the undisputed king of this verdant realm, it commands respect and awe from all creatures that share its lush, vibrant kingdom.
    </figcaption>
  </figure>
  <section id="tribute-info">
    <h3 id="headline">Here's a time line of the Lion King:</h3>
  <ul class="timeline">
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>0 - 3 Months: Early Childhood</h3>
      <p><strong>Birth:</strong> The Lion King is born in a secluded den, blind and helpless.</p>
      <p><strong>Nursing:</strong> Relies on its mother’s milk for nourishment.</p>
      <p><strong>First Steps:</strong> Begins to open eyes and take its first steps around the den.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>3 - 6 Months: Learning and Exploration</h3>
      <p><strong>Weaning:</strong> Starts eating meat provided by the mother.</p>
      <p><strong>Play:</strong> Engages in playful activities with siblings, honing hunting and fighting skills.</p>
      <p><strong>Exploration:</strong> Begins venturing out of the den, exploring the immediate surroundings under the watchful eye of the mother.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>6 - 18 Months: Growing and Training</h3>
      <p><strong>Learning to Hunt:</strong> Accompanies the pride on hunts, observing and learning the techniques.</p>
      <p><strong>Social Integration:</strong> Starts interacting more with other pride members, understanding social hierarchies.</p>
      <p><strong>First Hunts:</strong> Attempts small hunts independently, often with mixed success.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>18 - 24 Months: Adolescence</h3>
      <p><strong>Independence:</strong> Gains more independence, spending less time with the mother.</p>
      <p><strong>Practice Hunts:</strong> Becomes more proficient in hunting, often joining group hunts.</p>
      <p><strong>Challenges:</strong> Faces challenges from other young lions, learning to defend itself and assert dominance.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>2 - 3 Years: Young Adulthood</h3>
      <p><strong>Growth:</strong> Reaches near full size, with the mane beginning to develop prominently.</p>
      <p><strong>Roaming:</strong> Starts to roam further from the pride, sometimes temporarily leaving to explore.</p>
      <p><strong>First Mating Attempts:</strong> Begins to show interest in mating, though often deterred by dominant males.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>3 - 5 Years: Asserting Dominance</h3>
      <p><strong>Territorial Roaming:</strong> Frequently challenges other males for territory and pride control.</p>
      <p><strong>First Conquest:</strong> Successfully takes over a pride, establishing itself as the dominant male.</p>
      <p><strong>Mating:</strong> Mates with lionesses in the pride, beginning to sire cubs.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>5 - 8 Years: Reigning as King</h3>
      <p><strong>Peak Dominance:</strong> At the height of its power, the Lion King rules the pride with authority.</p>
      <p><strong>Fatherhood:</strong> Actively sires and raises multiple cubs, ensuring the continuation of its lineage.</p>
      <p><strong>Territory Defense:</strong> Fiercely defends territory from rival males, maintaining control over resources and pride members.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>8 - 12 Years: Challenges and Decline</h3>
      <p><strong>Physical Decline:</strong> Begins to show signs of aging, with decreased agility and strength.</p>
      <p><strong>Rival Challenges:</strong> Faces increasing challenges from younger, stronger males.</p>
      <p><strong>Losing Control:</strong> May lose control of the pride to a rival, forced to live a more solitary life.</p>
    </li>
    <li class="timeline-item">
      <h3>12+ Years: Elder Statesman</h3>
      <p><strong>Solitary Life:</strong> If dethroned, lives a more solitary existence, often on the fringes of territory.</p>
      <p><strong>Legacy:</strong> Continues to roam and survive, passing on valuable survival skills to younger lions.</p>
      <p><strong>Final Days:</strong> Eventually succumbs to old age or injury, leaving behind a legacy of strength and leadership.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>
 <blockquote>
    "In the heart of the jungle, the Lion King prowls with regal authority, his golden mane a symbol of strength and dominance. As the undisputed ruler of this verdant realm, he commands respect and awe from all creatures that share his lush, vibrant kingdom."
  </blockquote>
